== INITIAL DEPLOYMENT

Prerequisits:
* ruby (ree-1.8.7-2011.03, ruby-1.9.2 p 180)
* postgresql (tested on  9.*)
* libxml-dev
* libmagick++
* libpq-dev

Environment setup:

  $ gem install bundler
  $ bundle install
  $ cp config/database.yml.example config/database.yml

Edit your database.yml. Fill it with dbname and user credentials.

Create development database.

  $ rake db:create
  $ rake db:migrate

== TESTING

After initial deployment everything is ready to run cucumber features.

  $ rake cucumber


== Installing prerequisits on ubuntu 11.04

Installing PostgreSQL9:

  $ sudo add-apt-repository ppa:pitti/postgresql
  $ sudo apt-get install postgresql-9.0
  $ sudo apt-get install libpq-dev

Adding user for accessing postgresql

 $ sudo -u postgres createuser --superuser $USER

Setup password for new user

 $ sudo -u postgres psql
 postgres=# \password $USER


Then you simply get sources and make bundle install;

== Deploying fake data
Put goods images into data/images/ directory of the project and run rake tasks

  rake db:create
  rake db:migrate
  rake db:seed
  rake db:seed:fake_data

